</span> is
<ul id="mwcg"><li id="mwcw">independent of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wavelength" title="Wavelength" id="mwdA">wavelength</a> (no <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Dispersion_relation" title="Dispersion relation" id="mwdQ">dispersion</a>)</li>
<li id="mwdg">independent of amplitude (<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Linear" title="Linear" id="mwdw" class="mw-redirect">linear</a> media, not <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Nonlinear" title="Nonlinear" id="mweA" class="mw-redirect">nonlinear</a>).<sup about="#mwt338" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-Helbig_3-0" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{"name":"Helbig"},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-Helbig-3"}}'><a href="./Wave#cite_note-Helbig-3" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 3;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[3]</span></a></sup></li></ul></li>
<li id="mweQ">with constant <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Waveform" title="Waveform" id="mweg">waveform</a>, or shape</li></ul>

<p id="mwew">This wave can then be described by the two-dimensional functions</p>

<dl id="mwfA"><dd id="mwfQ"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt272" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"u(x,t) = F(x - v \\ t)"}}' id="mwfg"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle u(x,t)=F(x-v\ t)}">
