<p id="mwgw">or, more generally, by <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./D'Alembert's_formula" title="D'Alembert's formula" id="mwhA">d'Alembert's formula</a>:<sup about="#mwt350" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-Graaf_4-0" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{"name":"Graaf"},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-Graaf-4"}}'><a href="./Wave#cite_note-Graaf-4" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 4;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[4]</span></a></sup></p>

<dl id="mwhQ"><dd id="mwhg"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt285" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\nu(x,t) = F(x-vt) + G(x+vt). \\,\n"}}' id="mwhw"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle u(x,t)=F(x-vt)+G(x+vt).\,}">
