  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/50d4fb5750c966429bc49057c9f3f54d270d64d0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.074ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\tilde {f}}(k)=\sigma e^{-\sigma ^{2}k^{2}/2}\ ."/></span><span about="#mwt364">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwAmg">The Gaussian in space therefore is made up of waves:</p>

<dl id="mwAmk"><dd id="mwAmo"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt366" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"f(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2 \\pi}} \\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} \\ \\tilde{f} (k) e^{ikx} \\ dk \\ ; "}}' id="mwAms"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle f(x)={\frac {1}{\sqrt {2\pi }}}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }\ {\tilde {f}}(k)e^{ikx}\ dk\ ;}">
  <semantics>
