<cite class="citation book" about="#mwt105" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Electromagnetic Radiation: Variational Methods, Waveguides and Accelerators"},"author1":{"wt":"Kimball A. Milton"},"author2":{"wt":"Julian Seymour Schwinger"},"url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/?id=x_h2rai2pYwC&amp;pg=PA16"},"page":{"wt":"16"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-3-540-29304-0"},"publisher":{"wt":"Springer"},"year":{"wt":"2006"},"quote":{"wt":"Thus, an arbitrary function &apos;&apos;f&apos;&apos;(&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;r&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;, &apos;&apos;t&apos;&apos;) can be synthesized by a proper superposition of the functions &apos;&apos;exp&apos;&apos;[i (&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;k·r&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;&apos;−ω&apos;&apos;t&apos;&apos;)]..."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA18">Kimball A. Milton; Julian Seymour Schwinger (2006). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/?id=x_h2rai2pYwC&amp;pg=PA16" id="mwA2A"><i id="mwA2E">Electromagnetic Radiation: Variational Methods, Waveguides and Accelerators</i></a>. Springer. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA2I"> </span>16. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwA2M">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA2Q"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-3-540-29304-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-3-540-29304-0" id="mwA2U">978-3-540-29304-0</a>. <q id="mwA2Y">Thus, an arbitrary function <i id="mwA2c">f</i>(<i id="mwA2g"><b id="mwA2k">r</b></i>, <i id="mwA2o">t</i>) can be synthesized by a proper superposition of the functions <i id="mwA2s">exp</i>[i (<i id="mwA2w"><b id="mwA20">k·r</b></i>−ω<i id="mwA24">t</i>)]...</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Electromagnetic+Radiation%3A+Variational+Methods%2C+Waveguides