</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Newton-23" id="cite_note-Newton-23"><a href="./Wave#cite_ref-Newton_23-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Newton-23" class="mw-reference-text">

<cite class="citation book" about="#mwt120" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Newton"},"first":{"wt":"Isaac"},"year":{"wt":"1704"},"authorlink":{"wt":"Isaac Newton"},"title":{"wt":"Opticks: Or, A treatise of the Reflections, Refractions, Inflexions and Colours of Light. Also Two treatises of the Species and Magnitude of Curvilinear Figures"},"page":{"wt":"118"},"location":{"wt":"London"},"chapter":{"wt":"Prop VII Theor V"},"quote":{"wt":"All the Colours in the Universe which are made by Light... are either the Colours of homogeneal Lights, or compounded of these..."},"volume":{"wt":"1"},"chapter-url":{"wt":"http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3362k.image.f128.pagination"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA3o"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Isaac_Newton" title="Isaac Newton" id="mwA3s">Newton, Isaac</a> (1704). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3362k.image.f128.pagination" id="mwA3w">"Prop VII Theor V"</a>. <i id="mwA30">Opticks: Or, A treatise of the Reflections, Refractions, Inflexions and Colours of Light. Also Two treatises of the Species and Magnitude of Curvilinear Figures</i>. <b id="mwA34">1</b>. London. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA38"> </span>118. <q id="mwA4A">All the Colours in the Universe which are made by Light... are either the Colours of homogeneal Lights, or compounded of these...</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Prop+VII+Theor+V&amp;rft.btitle=Opticks%3A+Or%2C+A+treatise+of+the+Reflections%2C+Refractions%2C+Inflexions+and+Colours+of+Light.+Also+Two+treatises+of+the+Species+and+Magnitude+of+Curvilinear+Figures&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=118&amp;rft.date=1704&amp;rft.aulast=Newton&amp;rft.aufirst=Isaac&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgallica.bnf.fr%2Fark%3A%2F12148%2Fbpt6k3362k.image.f128.pagination&amp;rfr